subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Light green specimens with red stains on gnathopod 2 (
Fig 8
). Ovigerous females carrying red eggs. Antenna 1 accessory flagellum with 7 articles. Antenna 2 cone gland not reaching the end of article 3 (
Fig 10
). Eyes rounded (
Fig 9
). Coxa 1 anteroventral corner rounded produced (
Fig 12
). Gnathopod 1 carpus longer than propodus, posterior margin with plumose setae (
Fig 12
). Gnathopod 2 propodus palm with medial excavation and molar shaped hump, dactyl inner margin acutely produced (
Fig 11
). Telson deeply cleft (about 70%) telsonic lobes truncate with 5 stout setae longer than telson (
Fig 14
).
